{"title_page": "Jigme Wangchuck", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Jigme Wangchuk}}\n{{Infobox Monarch \n| name = Jigme Wangcock<br/>[[Image:Jigme Wangchuck Name.svg]]\n| title          = [[List of rulers of Bhutan|Druk Gyalpo]]\n| image          = Bhutan-Jigme-Wangchuck.jpg\n| caption        =\n| succession  = [[Druk Gyalpo|King of Bhutan]]\n| reign          = 26 August 1926 \u2013 30 March 1952\n| coronation     = 14 March 1927 <ref name=\"Royal Ark\">[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan3.htm Royal Ark]</ref>\n| predecessor    = [[Ugyen Wangchuck]]\n| successor      = [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]]\n| spouse         = 1st consort-[[Phuntsho Choden]]<br/>2nd consort-[[Pema Dechen]]\n| issue          = King [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]]<br/>Princess Choki Wangmo Wangchuck<br/>Prince Namgyel Wangchuck<br/>Princess Deki Yangzom Wangchuck <br/>Princess Pema Choden Wangchuck\n| royal house    = [[House of Wangchuck]]\n| father         = [[Ugyen Wangchuck]]\n| mother         = [[Tsundue Pema Lhamo]]\n| birth_date  = \n 1905\n| birth_place = Kuenga Rabten Palace\n| death_date  = {{death date|1952|3|30|df=y}} (aged 47)\n| death_place = Kuenga Rabten Palace, [[Dragteng Gewog]], [[Trongsa District|Trongsa]]<ref>[https://www.bhutanculturalatlas.org/1113/culture/sites-structures/dzongs-palaces/kuenga-rabten-palace/ www.bhutanculturalatlas.org]</ref>\n| place of burial= Cremated at [[Kurjey Lhakhang]]\n| religion = [[Buddhism]]\n}}\n\n'''Jigme Wangcock''' ([[Dzongkha]]: \u0f60\u0f47\u0f72\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f42, [[Wylie transliteration|Wylie]]: '' 'jigs med dbang phyug''; 1905 \u2013 30 March 1952) was the [[Druk Gyalpo]] or king of [[Bhutan]] from 21 August 1926, until his death. He was the eldest son of King [[Ugyen Wangchuck]] and was educated in English, Hindi and Buddhist literature.\n\n{{Wangchuck Kings of Bhutan}}\n\nUnder his reign, Bhutan continued to maintain almost complete isolation from the outside world, maintaining only limited relations with the [[British Raj]] in [[India]]. He was succeeded by his son, [[Jigme Dorji Wangcock]].<ref name=\"researchgate.net\">[https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lham_Dorji/publication/262373968_WANGCHUCK_DYNASTY_100_Years_of_Enlightened_Monarchy_in_Bhutan/links/0deec5376bf6ebc25e000000.pdf WANGCHUCK DYNASTY. 100 Years of Enlightened Monarchy in Bhutan. Lham Dorji]</ref>\n\n==Children==\nThe Second King, Jigme Wangchuck, had five children with his two cross cousins, ''Ashi'' [[Phuntsho Choden]] and her sister, ''Ashi'' [[Pema Dechen]]:<ref name=\"researchgate.net\"/>\n\n* The Third King (Druk Gyalpo) [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]] (by his first wife). \n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Choki Wangmo Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n* Prince (Druk Gyalsey) Namgyel Wangchuck, 26th ''[[Penlop]]'' of [[Paro District|Paro]] (by his second wife).\n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Deki Yangzom Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Pema Choden Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n\nPrincess Choki Wangmo Wangchuck has two daughters, ''Ashi'' Deki Choden and ''Ashi'' Sonam Yulgyal.\n\nPrincess Deki Yangzom Wangchuck has five children; ''Ashi'' Lhazen Nizal Rica, ''Dasho'' Jigme Namgyal, ''Dasho'' Wangchuck Dorji Namgyal, ''Ashi'' Yiwang Pindarica and ''Ashi'' Namzay Kumutha.\n\nPrincess Pema Choden Wangchuck has four children; ''Ashi'' Namden, ''Dasho'' Namgyel Dawa ([[Tulku]] Namgyel [[Rinpoche]]), ''Dasho'' Wangchen Dawa (Kathok Situ [[Rinpoche]]) and  ''Dasho'' Leon Rabten.\n\n==Honours==\n=== National honours ===\n* {{Flag|Bhutan}} :\n** [[File:Maharaja Ugyen Wangchuck Medal.gif|50px]] Maharaja Ugyen Wangchuck Medal 1st class in gold (17/11/1909).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n\n=== Foreign honours ===\n\n* {{Flag|British Raj}} :\n** [[File:King George V Coronation Medal ribbon.png|50px]] [[Delhi Durbar]] Silver Medal (12/12/1911).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n** [[File:Order of the Indian Empire Ribbon.svg|50px]] Companion of the [[Order of the Indian Empire]] (CIE - 11/03/1927).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/33256/pages/1601 |accessdate=2011-08-11 |date=1927-03-11 |title=Central Chancery of the Orders of Knighthood |newspaper=[[London Gazette]] |volume=33256 |page=1601 |format=PDF}}</ref>\n** [[File:Order of the Indian Empire Ribbon.svg|50px]] Honorary Knight Commander of the [[Order of the Indian Empire]] (KCIE - 03/06/1930).<ref>[http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/33611/supplements/3477 London Gazette, 3 June 1930]</ref>  \n* {{Flag|United Kingdom}} :\n** [[File:GeorgeVSilverJubileum-ribbon.png|50px]] [[King George V Silver Jubilee Medal]] (06/05/1935).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n** [[File:GeorgeVICoronationRibbon.png|50px]] [[King George VI Coronation Medal]] (12/05/1937).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n\nJejeiwka\n\n==See also==\n* [[House of Wangchuck]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan2.htm Royal Ark] The Wangchuk Dynasty GENEALOGY\n*[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan3.htm Royal Ark] The Wangchuk Dynasty GENEALOGY\n\n;Notes\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Wangchuck]]||1905||30 March 1952}}\n{{s-reg|}}\n{{succession box \n| before=[[Ugyen Wangchuck]] \n| title=[[List of rulers of Bhutan|King of Bhutan]] \n| after=[[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]] \n| years=1926\u20131952\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Rulers of Bhutan}}\n{{History of Bhutan}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wangchuck, Jigme}}\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1952 deaths]]\n[[Category:Bhutanese monarchs]]\n[[Category:World War II political leaders]]\n[[Category:Honorary Knights Commander of the Order of the Indian Empire]]\n[[Category:Buddhist monarchs]]\n[[Category:House of Wangchuck]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Order of the Indian Empire]]\n\n\n{{Bhutan-bio-stub}}\n{{Asia-royal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Jigme Wangchuk}}\n{{Infobox Monarch \n| name = Jigme Wangchuck<br/>[[Image:Jigme Wangchuck Name.svg]]\n| title          = [[List of rulers of Bhutan|Druk Gyalpo]]\n| image          = Bhutan-Jigme-Wangchuck.jpg\n| caption        =\n| succession  = [[Druk Gyalpo|King of Bhutan]]\n| reign          = 26 August 1926 \u2013 30 March 1952\n| coronation     = 14 March 1927 <ref name=\"Royal Ark\">[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan3.htm Royal Ark]</ref>\n| predecessor    = [[Ugyen Wangchuck]]\n| successor      = [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]]\n| spouse         = 1st consort-[[Phuntsho Choden]]<br/>2nd consort-[[Pema Dechen]]\n| issue          = King [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]]<br/>Princess Choki Wangmo Wangchuck<br/>Prince Namgyel Wangchuck<br/>Princess Deki Yangzom Wangchuck <br/>Princess Pema Choden Wangchuck\n| royal house    = [[House of Wangchuck]]\n| father         = [[Ugyen Wangchuck]]\n| mother         = [[Tsundue Pema Lhamo]]\n| birth_date  = \n 1905\n| birth_place = Kuenga Rabten Palace\n| death_date  = {{death date|1952|3|30|df=y}} (aged 47)\n| death_place = Kuenga Rabten Palace, [[Dragteng Gewog]], [[Trongsa District|Trongsa]]<ref>[https://www.bhutanculturalatlas.org/1113/culture/sites-structures/dzongs-palaces/kuenga-rabten-palace/ www.bhutanculturalatlas.org]</ref>\n| place of burial= Cremated at [[Kurjey Lhakhang]]\n| religion = [[Buddhism]]\n}}\n\n'''Jigme Wangchuck''' ([[Dzongkha]]: \u0f60\u0f47\u0f72\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f56\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f42, [[Wylie transliteration|Wylie]]: '' 'jigs med dbang phyug''; 1905 \u2013 30 March 1952) was the [[Druk Gyalpo]] or king of [[Bhutan]] from 21 August 1926, until his death. He was the eldest son of King [[Ugyen Wangchuck]] and was educated in English, Hindi and Buddhist literature.\n\n{{Wangchuck Kings of Bhutan}}\n\nUnder his reign, Bhutan continued to maintain almost complete isolation from the outside world, maintaining only limited relations with the [[British Raj]] in [[India]]. He was succeeded by his son, [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]].<ref name=\"researchgate.net\">[https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lham_Dorji/publication/262373968_WANGCHUCK_DYNASTY_100_Years_of_Enlightened_Monarchy_in_Bhutan/links/0deec5376bf6ebc25e000000.pdf WANGCHUCK DYNASTY. 100 Years of Enlightened Monarchy in Bhutan. Lham Dorji]</ref>\n\n==Children==\nThe Second King, Jigme Wangchuck, had five children with his two cross cousins, ''Ashi'' [[Phuntsho Choden]] and her sister, ''Ashi'' [[Pema Dechen]]:<ref name=\"researchgate.net\"/>\n\n* The Third King (Druk Gyalpo) [[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]] (by his first wife). \n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Choki Wangmo Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n* Prince (Druk Gyalsey) Namgyel Wangchuck, 26th ''[[Penlop]]'' of [[Paro District|Paro]] (by his second wife).\n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Deki Yangzom Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n* Princess (Druk Gyalsem) Pema Choden Wangchuck (by his second wife).\n\nPrincess Choki Wangmo Wangchuck has two daughters, ''Ashi'' Deki Choden and ''Ashi'' Sonam Yulgyal.\n\nPrincess Deki Yangzom Wangchuck has five children; ''Ashi'' Lhazen Nizal Rica, ''Dasho'' Jigme Namgyal, ''Dasho'' Wangchuck Dorji Namgyal, ''Ashi'' Yiwang Pindarica and ''Ashi'' Namzay Kumutha.\n\nPrincess Pema Choden Wangchuck has four children; ''Ashi'' Namden, ''Dasho'' Namgyel Dawa ([[Tulku]] Namgyel [[Rinpoche]]), ''Dasho'' Wangchen Dawa (Kathok Situ [[Rinpoche]]) and  ''Dasho'' Leon Rabten.\n\n==Honours==\n=== National honours ===\n* {{Flag|Bhutan}} :\n** [[File:Maharaja Ugyen Wangchuck Medal.gif|50px]] Maharaja Ugyen Wangchuck Medal 1st class in gold (17/11/1909).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n\n=== Foreign honours ===\n\n* {{Flag|British Raj}} :\n** [[File:King George V Coronation Medal ribbon.png|50px]] [[Delhi Durbar]] Silver Medal (12/12/1911).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n** [[File:Order of the Indian Empire Ribbon.svg|50px]] Companion of the [[Order of the Indian Empire]] (CIE - 11/03/1927).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/33256/pages/1601 |accessdate=2011-08-11 |date=1927-03-11 |title=Central Chancery of the Orders of Knighthood |newspaper=[[London Gazette]] |volume=33256 |page=1601 |format=PDF}}</ref>\n** [[File:Order of the Indian Empire Ribbon.svg|50px]] Honorary Knight Commander of the [[Order of the Indian Empire]] (KCIE - 03/06/1930).<ref>[http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/33611/supplements/3477 London Gazette, 3 June 1930]</ref>  \n* {{Flag|United Kingdom}} :\n** [[File:GeorgeVSilverJubileum-ribbon.png|50px]] [[King George V Silver Jubilee Medal]] (06/05/1935).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n** [[File:GeorgeVICoronationRibbon.png|50px]] [[King George VI Coronation Medal]] (12/05/1937).<ref name=\"Royal Ark\"/>\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Jigme Wangchuck'''\n|2= 2. [[Ugyen Wangchuck]]\n|3= 3. [[Tsundue Pema Lhamo]]\n|4= 4. [[Jigme Namgyal (Bhutan)|Jigme Namgyal, 10th ''Trongsa Penlop'' and 48th ''Druk Desi'']]\n|5= 5. Pema Choki \n|6= 6. Kunzang Thinley, ''[[Dzongpen|Dzongpon]]'' of [[Thimphu District|Thimphu]]\n|7= 7. Sangay Drolma\n|8= 8. Pila Gonpo Wangyal (= 24)\n|9= 9. Sonam Pedzom (= 25)\n|10= 10. Ugyen Phuntsho, 8th ''[[Penlop of Trongsa|Trongsa Penlop]]''\n|11= 11. Rinchen Pelmo\n|12= 12. Dungkar Gyeltshen, 11th ''[[Penlop of Trongsa|Trongsa Penlop]]''\n|13= \n|14= 14. Kencho Wangdu \n|15=  \n|16= 16. Padma\n|17= \n|18= \n|19= \n|20=  \n|21= \n|22= 22. Sonam Drugyel, 31st ''[[Druk Desi]]'' \n|23= \n|24= 24. Pila Gonpo Wangyal (= 8)\n|25= 25. Sonam Pedzom (= 9)\n|26= \n|27=  \n|28= \n|29=  \n|30= \n|31=  \n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[House of Wangchuck]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan2.htm Royal Ark] The Wangchuk Dynasty GENEALOGY\n*[http://www.royalark.net/Bhutan/bhutan3.htm Royal Ark] The Wangchuk Dynasty GENEALOGY\n\n;Notes\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Wangchuck]]||1905||30 March 1952}}\n{{s-reg|}}\n{{succession box \n| before=[[Ugyen Wangchuck]] \n| title=[[List of rulers of Bhutan|King of Bhutan]] \n| after=[[Jigme Dorji Wangchuck]] \n| years=1926\u20131952\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Rulers of Bhutan}}\n{{History of Bhutan}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wangchuck, Jigme}}\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1952 deaths]]\n[[Category:Bhutanese monarchs]]\n[[Category:World War II political leaders]]\n[[Category:Honorary Knights Commander of the Order of the Indian Empire]]\n[[Category:Buddhist monarchs]]\n[[Category:House of Wangchuck]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Order of the Indian Empire]]\n\n\n{{Bhutan-bio-stub}}\n{{Asia-royal-stub}}\n", "name_user": "173.218.102.31", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jigme_Wangchuck"}
{"title_page": "The Devil Wears Prada (band)", "text_new": "{{redirect|TDWP|other uses of the abbreviation|The Devil Wears Prada (disambiguation)}}\n{{pp-semi|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = The Devil Wears Prada\n| image               = The devil wears prada promo.jpg\n| caption             = The Devil Wears Prada in 2010. From left to right: Daniel Williams, Andy Trick, Mike Hranica, James Baney, Jeremy DePoyster and Chris Rubey.\n| image_size          = \n| landscape           = Yes\n| background          = group_or_band\n| origin              = [[Dayton, Ohio]], U.S.\n| genre               = [[Metalcore]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reviewrinserepeat.com/artist/the-devil-wears-prada/album/dead-throne/review |title=The Devil Wears Prada - Dead Throne |publisher=Review Rinse Repeat |date=September 2, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rhapsody.com/artist/the-devil-wears-prada/album/with-roots-above-and-branches-below |title=With Roots Above And Branches Below : The Devil Wears Prada |publisher=Rhapsody}}</ref><ref name=\"LoudwireThrone\">{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/the-devil-wears-prada-dead-throne-album-review/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada, 'Dead Throne' |publisher=[[Loudwire]] |date=September 13, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"audioinkradiothrone\">{{cite web |url=http://audioinkradio.com/2011/09/the-devil-wears-prada-dead-throne-is-an-ambush-of-sound-album-review/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada \u2018Dead Throne\u2019 is an Ambush of Sound \u2013 Album Review |publisher=Audio Ink Radio |date=September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/cdreviews/fr/devilwearsplagu.htm |title=The Devil Wears Prada - Plagues Review |publisher=Chad Bowar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://killhipsters.com/2011/08/devil-wears-prada-dead-throne-album-review/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada - Dead Throne |publisher=killhipster |date=August 25, 2011 |access-date=February 7, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060538/http://killhipsters.com/2011/08/devil-wears-prada-dead-throne-album-review/ |archive-date=September 21, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"ReflectionsThrone\">{{cite web |url=http://www.reflectionsofdarkness.com/artists-a-e-cdreviews-131/10035-cd-review-devil-wears-prada-the-dead-throne.html |title=Devil Wears Prada, The - Dead Throne |publisher=Reflections of Darkness |date=September 12, 2011}}</ref> {{nowrap|[[Christian metal]]}}<ref>{{cite web|first=Kim|last=Jones|title=Top 8 Christian Metal Bands|url=http://christianmusic.about.com/od/metalandhardrock/tp/Top-Christian-Metal-Bands.htm|publisher=[[About.com]]|accessdate=January 29, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=An interview with Mike Hranica of The Devil Wears Prada|url=http://www.silive.com/teens/index.ssf/2009/04/an_interview_with_mike_hranica.html|last=Rentas|first=Brian|publisher=SILive.com|date=April 9, 2009|accessdate=March 24, 2016|quote=}}</ref>\n| years_active        = 2005\u2013present\n| label               = {{hlist|[[Rise Records|Rise]]|[[Ferret Music|Ferret]]|[[Warner Music Group|Warner Music]]|[[Roadrunner Records|Roadrunner]]|[[Solid State Records|Solid State]]}}\n| associated_acts     = \n| website             = {{URL|http://tdwpband.com}}\n| current_members     = Jeremy DePoyster<br />Mike Hranica<br />Andy Trick<br />Kyle Sipress<br>Jonathan Gering<br>[[Giuseppe Capolupo]]\n\n| past_members        = James Baney<br />Chris Rubey<br />Daniel Williams\n}}\n\n'''The Devil Wears Prada''' is an American [[Christian metal#Metalcore|Christian metalcore]] band from [[Dayton, Ohio]], formed in 2005. It consists of members Mike Hranica (vocals, additional guitar), Jeremy DePoyster (rhythm guitar, vocals), Kyle Sipress (lead guitar, backing vocals), Andy Trick (bass), Jonathan Gering (keyboards), and [[Giuseppe Capolupo]] (drums). The band had maintained its original lineup until keyboardist James Baney left the band. To date, the group has released seven full-length albums: ''[[Dear Love: A Beautiful Discord]]'' (2006),  ''[[Plagues (album)|Plagues]]'' (2007), ''[[With Roots Above and Branches Below]]'' (2009), ''[[Dead Throne]]'' (2011), ''[[8:18]]'' (2013) ''[[Transit Blues]]'' (2016), and ''[[The Act (album)|The Act]]'' (2019) as well as two EPs, one DVD, sixteen singles, and thirteen music videos.\n\n==History==\n\n===Formation and first releases (2005\u20132006)===\n\nThe Devil Wears Prada was founded during 2005 in [[Dayton Ohio]];<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p822710}}</ref> they derived their band name from [[The Devil Wears Prada (novel)|the story of the same title]].<ref name=\"highwiredaze.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.highwiredaze.com/thedevilwearprada.htm|title=The Devil Wears Prada &gt; Biography|work=High Wire Daze|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226194455/http://www.highwiredaze.com/thedevilwearprada.htm|archivedate=February 26, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Being founded with all Christian members and maintaining a theme that represents their religion, the group played their first show in 2005 with a fill-in bassist and only one guitarist. Rhythm guitarist Jeremy Depoyster and bassist Andy Trick joined the band soon afterward. They continued playing at local areas in Dayton before recording their demo later in the year which was titled ''Patterns of a Horizon''.<ref name=desertnews>{{cite web|last=Scott|first=Iwasaki|title=Metalcore band 'The Devil Wears Prada' spreads Christian message|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/700015813/Metalcore-band-The-Devil-Wears-Prada-spreads-Christian-message.html|work=Deseret News|accessdate=July 18, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOne year after the group recorded their demo and trialed for record labels, [[Rise Records]] took the band in with a contract. The band was unsatisfied with the demo so they re-recorded all of the tracks from the demo for their debut full-length album, ''[[Dear Love: A Beautiful Discord]]''. The album was recorded with [[Joey Sturgis]], at The Foundation Recording Studio held in [[Connersville, Indiana]] and it was released on August 22, 2006. The record's final track features guest vocals, courtesy of Cole Wallace who was formerly part of the band [[Gwen Stacy (band)|Gwen Stacy]]. With the release of the album, the band then began touring in multiple areas throughout the country, most notably at 2006's [[Cornerstone Festival]] after being recognized as a newer key musical group to Christian metal.\n\n===''Plagues'' (2006\u20132008)===\n[[File:TheDevilWearsPradaCornerstone.jpg|thumb|The Devil Wears Prada performing at [[Cornerstone Festival]], a [[Christian music festival]]]]\n\nWith ''Dear Love'' released at the end of the summer of 2006, The Devil Wears Prada already had songs for their second album prepared by winter of the same year. With a recording duration lasting from that time and leading into spring of 2007, the band's second album, ''[[Plagues (album)|Plagues]]'' met its completion by the summer and was released on August 21, 2007. The demo version of their song \"HTML Rulez D00d\" was placed on the band's Myspace profile on January 1, 2007 for promotion of the record and on July 11, [[AbsolutePunk]] began to stream their song \"Don't Dink and Drance\", which led to further exposure for the band.<ref name=\"AbsolutePunk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=250178|title=The Devil Wears Prada track listing |last=Foucart|first=Jon|work=[[AbsolutePunk]]}}</ref>\n\nThe songs from the album \"HTML Rulez D00d\" and \"Hey John, What's Your Name Again?\" were released as the album's two singles, both of which spawned music videos that aired on television channels such as MTV and [[Fuse TV|Fuse]]. ''Plagues'' peaked at No.&nbsp;57 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] on September 8, 2007<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=the devil wears prada|chart=all}} Discography index] ''Billboard'' 200</ref> and has been considered a great success since its original release, selling more than 30,000 copies more than their debut album, ''[[Dear Love: A Beautiful Discord]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interpunk.com/item.cfm?Item=149863& |title='&#39;Plagues'&#39; at |publisher=Interpunk.com |accessdate=January 1, 2012}}</ref> It was re-released on October 28, 2008 in a [[digipak]] form that includes a DVD in which features the music videos for album's two singles as well as footage of The Devil Wears Prada playing at 2008's [[Warped Tour]] and Ultimatour. Later in the year, the band was interviewed by East Coast Romper, and stated that their primary influences are [[Underoath]] and [[Still Remains]], which was mistaken on their official website due to it incorrectly stating that they were not influenced by these bands. The band recorded a cover of the rap song \"[[Still Fly]]\", originally written and performed by [[Big Tymers]], the cover song was released on the compilation album ''[[Punk Goes Crunk]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thealbumproject.net/2008/04/full-review-va-punk-goes-crunk/ |title=Full Review: V/A \u2013 Punk Goes Crunk |publisher=The Album Project |accessdate=January 1, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20080704035817/http://thealbumproject.net/2008/04/full-review-va-punk-goes-crunk/ |archivedate=July 4, 2008 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===''With Roots Above and Branches Below'' (2008\u20132010)===\nThe Devil Wears Prada began writing and recording their third album ''[[With Roots Above and Branches Below]]'' after attending 2008's [[Warped Tour]]. Prior to recording and production of it, vocalist Mike Hranica stated \"Expect a much heavier and more epic record\". Keyboardist, James Baney, also announced that their new album would be more mechanical but still containing their same distinct style whereas drummer, Daniel Williams, claimed that the new album would be \"crazier and wilder\" than their previous albums. In Autumn 2008, they debuted a song off of the upcoming record while on tour with [[Underoath]], [[The Famine]], [[Saosin]], [[P.O.S (rapper)|P.O.S]], and [[Person L]].<ref>[http://www.metalunderground.com/news/details.cfm?newsid=38714 Underoath's Entire New Album and Video Online] in Metal News</ref> The Devil Wears Prada performed with [[A Day to Remember]], [[Sky Eats Airplane]] and [[Emarosa]]. They have also performed at [[Warped Tour 2009|2009's Warped Tour]] to promote the release of ''With Roots Above and Branches Below''.<ref>[http://eventful.com/performers/the-devil-wears-prada-/P0-001-000010066-4 Performers: The Devil Wears Prada] Eventful</ref> On March 13, the group released a song from the album prior to its release entitled \"Dez Moines\". Also before the release, the purchaser was given the option to receive several pre-ordered packages. One deal that features the album, a DVD and a shirt also includes a card with a code that let the purchaser download \"Dez Moines\", and \"Assistant to the Regional Manager\". The band launched their official website and released ''With Roots Above and Branches Below'' both on May 5, 2009. The sales of the album have been very satisfactory which brought it to position No.&nbsp;11 on the ''Billboard'' 200 for top albums upon its release.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=the devil wears prada|chart=Billboard 200}} The Devil Wears Prada charting at No.&nbsp;11]. ''Billboard''</ref> The song \"Dez Moines\" was released as downloadable content for the video game ''[[Guitar Hero World Tour]]'' on May 7, as well as the song \"Hey John, What's Your Name Again?\" was released as downloadable content for ''[[Rock Band (video game)|Rock Band]]'' and ''[[Rock Band 2]]'' on June 30, 2009.<ref>[http://www.smnnews.com/2009/04/29/unearth-chimaira-the-devil-wears-prada-featuring-on-guitar-hero-world-tour/ UNEARTH, CHIMAIRA, THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA FEATURING ON GUITAR HERO WORLD TOUR] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322225404/http://www.smnnews.com/2009/04/29/unearth-chimaira-the-devil-wears-prada-featuring-on-guitar-hero-world-tour/ |date=March 22, 2012 }} SMN News</ref><ref>[http://www.rockband.com/zine/tag/the-devil-wears-prada The Zine] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090819021523/http://www.rockband.com/zine/tag/the-devil-wears-prada |date=August 19, 2009 }} Rock Band</ref>\n\nAs well as performing at the main stage of Warped Tour 2009, The Devil Wears Prada as well played at the iMatter Festival in [[Elmira, New York]]. On June 13, they performed the song \"Danger: Wildman\" for the first time in concert. Vocalist Mike Hranica, managed a clothing company called Shipshape Roolz Clothing in which he sponsored and endorsed bands. A fraction of Shipshape's scale money was donated to charities such as Skate 4 Cancer. As of September 29, 2009 the clothing line was shut down and its online store changed its name to Traditiona, due to \"legal issues.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shipshaperoolz.com/ |title=Shipshape Roolz Clothing |publisher=Shipshaperoolz.com |accessdate=January 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Camo Logo Tee Shirt \u2013 S |url=http://traditiona.com/ |title=Traditiona.com |publisher=Traditiona.com |accessdate=January 1, 2012}}</ref> From November 23 to December 21, 2009 the band toured with [[All That Remains (band)|All That Remains]]<ref>[http://puregrainaudio.com/news/all-that-remains-the-devil-wears-prada-announce-tour ALL THAT REMAINS & THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA ANNOUNCE TOUR]. PureGrainAudio</ref><ref>[http://www.livedaily.com/news/all-that-remains-tickets-and-tour-dates-all-that-remains-the-devil-wears-prada-hook-up-for-fall-trek-20245.html All That Remains, The Devil Wears Prada hook up for fall trek]. LiveDaily.</ref> and from February 4 to March 21, 2010 they were included on a tour headlined by [[Killswitch Engage]] and opened by [[Dark Tranquillity]].<ref>[http://www.alternativepress.com/news/8301.htm Killswitch Engage/The Devil Wears Prada tour dates revealed]. [[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]. Retrieved 1-12-10</ref><ref>[http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.Net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=131814 KILLSWITCH ENGAGE, THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA To Team Up For U.S. Tour] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091216072818/http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=131814 |date=December 16, 2009 }}. [[Blabbermouth.net]]. Retrieved 1-12-10</ref>\n\nAt the beginning of 2010, it was announced that The Devil Wears Prada were voted as 2009's Band of the Year by readers of ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]'' and appeared on the cover.<ref>[http://altpress.com/apmag/259.htm The Devil Wears Prada article] at [[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]].</ref> On February 12, 2010 the group confirmed the production for the \"Assistant to the Regional Manager\" music video,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noisecreep.com/2010/02/12/behind-the-scenes-at-the-devil-wears-pradas-almost-shocking-v/|title=Behind the Scenes at the Devil Wears Prada\u2019s \u2018Almost Shocking\u2019 Video Shoot|work=Noisecreep|accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref> this led to its release on April 6, 2010 where it was premiered on ''[[Headbangers Ball]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noisecreep.com/2010/04/07/the-devil-wears-prada-assistant-to-the-regional-manager-video/|title=The Devil Wears Prada, \u2018Assistant to the Regional Manager\u2019 \u2014 Video|work=Noisecreep|accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://revolverblips.dailyradar.com/video/the-devil-wears-prada-assistant-to-the-regional/ The Devil Wears Prada \u2013 Assistant To The Regional Manager \u2013 Metal] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100818215203/http://revolverblips.dailyradar.com/video/the-devil-wears-prada-assistant-to-the-regional/ |date=August 18, 2010 }} Revolver</ref>\n\n===''Zombie'' EP and ''Dead Throne'' (2010\u20132013)===\nIn an interview at the beginning of April with Lucy Alberts of ''Alternative Press'', the band revealed that they were recording an  [[extended play|EP]] before they begin their Back to the Roots Tour. The EP was described as a \"fun\" release with \"brutal\" songs in the vein of what will eventually become the band's forthcoming studio album.<ref>{{cite web| last = Albers| first = Lucy| title = Q&A: Mike Hranica of The Devil Wears Prada| work = [[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]] | date = April 9, 2010| url = http://altpress.com/features/qa_hranica.htm| accessdate =April 9, 2010}}</ref> The band's Back to the Roots Tour was presented by [[Rockstar (drink)|Rockstar]]. Mike Hranica stated \"One of the primary elements of the Back to the Roots Tour is playing a few ''[[Dear Love: A Beautiful Discord|Dear Love]]'' songs that we have not played in a long time, and probably will not play again or anytime soon.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Matt |url=http://www.noisecreep.com/2010/04/19/the-devil-wears-prada-back-to-the-roots-tour-dates/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada Back to the Roots Tour Dates |publisher=Noisecreep.com |date=May 11, 2010 |accessdate=January 1, 2012}}</ref> On June 11 it was announced that they have completed the recording of the EP,<ref>[http://www.theprp.com/2010/06/11/news/the-devil-wears-prada-finish-new-ep/ The Devil Wears Prada Finish New EP] The PRP</ref> the title for it was revealed as being ''[[Zombie (EP)|Zombie]]'' and was released on August 23.<ref name=\"Zombie AllMusic\">{{cite web| title = Zombie| work = [[AllMusic]]| url = {{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1841274|pure_url=yes}}| accessdate =June 28, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=142561 | publisher=Blabbermouth | title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA To Release 'Zombie' EP | date=July 5, 2010 | accessdate=July 10, 2010 }}</ref> After the completion and announcement of the EP, the band began their Back to the Roots Tour on June 25 as they planned.<ref>[http://www.thegauntlet.com/article/3824/18315/Devil%20Wears%20Prada,%20the.html THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA announces headlining tour] The Gauntlet</ref>\n\nBy January 2011, Hranica revealed in an interview with Tim Karan what the band's ideas and plans for their fourth full-length studio album would be. His comments were placed within comparison to their latest release (the ''Zombie'' EP and described that the record is \"a more heavy-focused sound from us. We think it would be smart to push that beefy, heavy songwriting [from ''Zombie''] into the new full-length...but with a strong blend of what we usually do with melody.\" The album was confirmed to not be a [[concept album]] \u2013 like their previous work on the ''Zombie'' EP \u2013 but would have an overall theme, focused on anti-[[idolatry]], which, according to Hranica, \"has been weighing on me lately.\"<ref>''The Devil Wears Prada'' \u2022 January 2011 \u2014 ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]''</ref> On June 13, ''Alternative Press'' began streaming a track, titled \"Born to Lose\", debuting off the upcoming album, and during the same month, the band signed with [[Roadrunner Records]].<ref name=\"Roadrunner\">{{cite web|title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA Signs With ROADRUNNER RECORDS \u2013 June 21, 2011|url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159710|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=October 7, 2011}}</ref> Vocalist, Hrancia offered his opinion of the new material, stating that it will contain \"the heavy aspects of the ''Zombie'' EP, meshed with the melody of the full-lengths. \u2018Born to Lose\u2019 captures some of those elements and serves as a comprehensive preview to the album.\" He ended his comments with; \"By all means I'd call it our most emotional, well-written album to date.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/exclusive_stream_the_devil_wears_pradas_born_to_lose/|title=Exclusive Stream: The Devil Wears Prada\u2019s \"Born To Lose\"|date=June 13, 2011|work=Alternative Press|accessdate=June 13, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe album's name was revealed to be ''[[Dead Throne]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/aptv/video/exclusive_the_devil_wears_prada_in-studio_and_album_title_reveal/|title=Exclusive: The Devil Wears Prada in-studio and album title reveal|date=June 24, 2011|work=Alternative Press|accessdate=June 24, 2011}}</ref> and was released on September 13, 2011 through [[Ferret Music]]. It has since become a critical and commercial success, where it peaked at number 10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/400338/devil-wears-prada/chart |title=The Devil Wears Prada - Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=May 16, 2014}}</ref> on the ''Billboard'' 200, selling 32,420 copies within its first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/467358/lady-antebellum-own-the-billboard-200-with-second-no-1-album |title=Lady Antebellum 'Own' the Billboard 200 With Second No.&nbsp;1 Album |work=Billboard |date=September 14, 2009 |accessdate=January 1, 2012}}</ref> ''Dead Throne'' also topped the [[Christian Albums|Christian]] and [[Independent Albums|Independent]] album charts, as well as peaking at number 3 on the [[Rock Albums Chart|Rock]] and [[Hard Rock Albums|Hard Rock]] album charts.<ref>{{cite web|title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA'S DEAD THRONE DEBUTS AT No.&nbsp;10 ON BILLBOARD'S TOP 200 |url=http://www.jesusfreakhideout.com/news/2011/09/21.THE%20DEVIL%20WEARS%20PRADAS%20DEAD%20THRONE%20DEBUTS%20AT%20No.10%20ON%20BILLBOARDS%20TOP%20200.asp |publisher=Jesus Freak Hideout|accessdate=September 29, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe band was confirmed for the [[Mayhem Festival]] tour at the beginning of 2012,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rockstarmayhemfest.com/blog/id/1845118 |title=Rockstar Mayhem Festival/Blog/2012 Dates Announced |publisher=Rockstarmayhemfest.com |accessdate=January 25, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111104152448/http://rockstarmayhemfest.com/blog/id/1845118 |archivedate=November 4, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> with [[Slayer]], [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]] and [[As I Lay Dying (band)|As I Lay Dying]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rockstarmayhemfest.com/bands |title=Rockstar Mayhem Bands Confirmed |publisher=Rockstarmayhemfest.com |accessdate=January 25, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031020243/http://rockstarmayhemfest.com/bands |archivedate=October 31, 2013 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> During this tour on February 22, 2012 keyboard player James Baney left the band.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yao|first=Keith|title=James Baney Leaves The Devil Wears Prada|url=http://lostinthesound.com/2012/02/james-baney-leaves-the-devil-wears-prada/|publisher=Lost in the Sound|accessdate=February 26, 2012}}</ref> The Devil Wears Prada will release a CD/DVD album, ''Dead and Alive''.<ref>{{cite web|last=The Devil Wears Prada Store|first=The Devil Wears Prada Store|title=Dead&Alive CD/DVD album|url=http://tdwpstore.com/store/show/M8FAQ|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120526121811/http://tdwpstore.com/store/show/M8FAQ|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 26, 2012|publisher=TDWP Store|accessdate=May 23, 2012}}</ref> The live album was released on June 26, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=The Devil Wears Prada Store|first=The Devil Wears Prada Store|title=Dead&Alive CD/DVD album|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/preorder/dead-alive/id532407524|publisher=iTunes Store|accessdate=June 6, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===''8:18'' (2013\u20132015)===\n[[File:The Devil Wears Prada-18.jpg|thumb|Vocalist Mike Hranica in 2013]]\nOn January 25, 2012 Mike Hranica announced in an interview with Noisecreep that the band is working on their fifth album and that the album will be darker than Dead Throne and lyrically more sad and miserable, Hranica also stated that guitarist Chris Rubey has come up with material that is absolutely relentless.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2013/01/25/news/the-devil-wears-pradas-mike-hranica-says-new-album-will-be-darker-than-dead-throne/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada\u2019s Mike Hranica Says New Album: \"Will Be Darker Than Dead Throne\" &#124; Theprp.com \u2013 Metal, Hardcore And Rock News, Reviews And More |publisher=Theprp.com |date= |accessdate=January 27, 2013}}</ref> Hranica went on to comment that he is very excited on the keyboard parts they've been working on since James Baney's departure, describing them as \"very dark and intense\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Jason Anton |url=http://www.noisecreep.com/2013/01/25/the-devil-wears-prada-new-album/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada Singer Mike Hranica on Their Upcoming Album (EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW) |publisher=Noisecreep |accessdate=January 27, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn February 20, 2013 the band announced that guitarist Chris Rubey missed the band's immediate touring with As I Lay Dying to tend to his newborn child. Samuel Penner of [[For Today (band)|For Today]] and [[In the Midst of Lions]] was Rubey's temporary replacement.<ref name=\"ITMOL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2013/02/20/news/the-devil-wears-prada-guitarist-chris-rubey-to-miss-immediate-live-dates/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada Guitarist Chris Rubey To Miss Immediate Live Dates &#124; Theprp.com \u2013 Metal, Hardcore And Rock News, Reviews And More |publisher=Theprp.com |date=February 20, 2013 |accessdate=June 15, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe Devil Wears Prada performed a new track titled \"Gloom\" at live shows, the final studio version of the song is on the group's latest studio album, which will see a fall release through [[Roadrunner Records]]. That album was produced by [[Matt Goldman]] ([[Underoath]], [[The Chariot (band)|The Chariot]]) with [[Killswitch Engage]] guitarist [[Adam Dutkiewicz]] executive producing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2013/03/01/news/the-devil-wears-prada-perform-new-song-gloom-footage-available/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada Perform New Song \"Gloom\", Footage Available &#124; Theprp.com \u2013 Metal, Hardcore And Rock News, Reviews And More |publisher=Theprp.com |date= |accessdate=June 15, 2013}}</ref> The new album was released on September 17, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2013/06/15/news/the-devil-wears-prada-reveal-new-album-release-date/ |title=The Devil Wears Prada Reveal New Album Release Date &#124; Theprp.com \u2013 Metal, Hardcore And Rock News, Reviews And More |publisher=Theprp.com |date= |accessdate=June 15, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIt was revealed on the band's Facebook that the title of the new album would be ''8:18''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/tdwp?hc_location=stream |title=The Devil Wears Prada Reveal New Album &#124; Facebook.com |publisher=Facebook.com |date= |accessdate=July 24, 2013}}</ref> Pre-orders began on July 30, 2013 and included the tracks \"Home for Grave\" and \"Martyrs\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sYdp1oyKOPg |title=The Devil Wears Prada - 8:18 Pre-Order Announcement |publisher=YouTube |date=July 24, 2013 |accessdate=September 20, 2013}}</ref> The lyric video \"Martyrs\" was released on July 30, 2013 on [[Rolling Stone]]<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/videos/the-devil-wears-prada-explore-isolation-in-martyrs-premiere-20130730 |title=The Devil Wears Prada Explore Isolation in 'Martyrs' \u2013 Premiere - Video |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=July 30, 2013 |accessdate=September 20, 2013}}</ref> and released on July 31, 2013 on [[YouTube]]'s official band page.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=27mTRnqMzxM |title=The Devil Wears Prada - Martyrs (Audio) |publisher=YouTube |date=July 31, 2013 |accessdate=September 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced in early 2014 that the band would be touring as part of the [[Warped Tour 2014]] on one of the main stages.{{Citation needed|date=January 2014}}\n\n=== Label changes, line-up instability and ''Transit Blues'' (2015\u20132018)===\nOn March 7, 2015 the band resigned to [[Rise Records]]. 10 days later, they announced the departure of founding guitarist Chris Rubey, and that they will be releasing a new EP titled ''[[Space (EP)|Space]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/the_devil_wears_prada_part_ways_with_guitarist_founding_member_chris_rubey|title=The Devil Wears Prada part ways with guitarist/founding member, Chris Rubey|work=Alternative Press|accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://propertyofzack.com/post/113922571353/the-devil-wears-prada-founding-member-chris-rubey|title=The Devil Wears Prada founding member Chris Rubey... \u2014 PropertyOfZack|work=propertyofzack.com|accessdate=March 19, 2015}}</ref> The band will also be releasing a 7\" vinyl on Record Store Day titled ''South of the City'' via Atlantic/Roadrunner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/the_devil_wears_prada_to_release_south_of_the_city_seven_inch|title=The Devil Wears Prada to release 'South Of The City' seven-inch - Alternative Press|work=Alternative Press}}</ref> On March 14, the band embarked on a tour for the five-year anniversary of their EP ''Zombie''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/the_devil_wears_prada_to_perform_zombie_in_full_on_zombie_5_tour|title=The Devil Wears Prada to perform 'Zombie' EP in full on Zombie 5 Tour - Alternative Press|work=Alternative Press}}</ref> The band has performed \"Supernova\", a song off ''Space'', and released it on June 18;<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jvNJPWnp7sQ|title=The Devil Wears Prada - Supernova (\"Space\" EP - Aug. 21st)|date=June 18, 2015|work=YouTube}}</ref> this was followed by another song, titled \"Alien\", on August 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ruP9jHSxp0U|title=The Devil Wears Prada - Alien|first=|last=riserecords|date=August 3, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=April 3, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> Before the EP was released, Hranica announced they had a new guitarist named Kyle Sipress, the band's former guitar tech.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/the-devil-wears-prada-mike-hranica-space-ep-new-guitarist-zombie-ep/|title=The Devil Wears Prada's Mike Hranica Talks ''Space'' EP, New Guitarist + Revisiting ''Zombie'' EP|publisher=[[Loudwire]]|first=Liz|last=Ramanand|date=April 30, 2015|accessdate=May 4, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"About\">{{cite web|url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/interviews/fl/The-Devil-Wears-Prada-Interview.htm|title=The Devil Wears Prada Interview|publisher=[[About.com]]|first=Chad|last=Bowar|date=August 18, 2015|accessdate=January 14, 2017}}</ref> The ''Space'' EP itself was released on August 21.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/the-devil-wears-prada-supernova-from-space-ep/|title=The Devil Wears Prada Unleash 'Supernova' From Upcoming 'Space' EP|work=Loudwire}}</ref>\nOn August 20, the band premiered a music video for the opening track, \"Planet A\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/new-the-devil-wears-prada-planet-a-video|title=Enter the Horrors of Space and Existence in The Devil Wears Prada's Video for \"Planet A\"|author=|date=August 20, 2015|website=vice.com|accessdate=April 3, 2018}}</ref>\nOn July 2, 2016, the band parted ways with drummer Daniel Williams.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/tdwp/posts/10154259717697618|title=The Devil Wears Prada announcement|publisher=[[Facebook]]|author=The Devil Wears Prada|date=July 2, 2016}}</ref>\nOn July 15, 2016, the band released a new song along with a music video called \"Daughter\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4ZrDSR81RE|title=The Devil Wears Prada - Daughter (Official Music Video)|first=|last=riserecords|date=July 15, 2016|publisher=|accessdate=April 3, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\nOn July 18, 2016, just a couple of days after they released \"Daughter\", the band announced their new record ''Transit Blues'' will be released on October 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/tdwp/photos/a.385511162617.162893.8591572617/10154302707202618/?type=3&ref=notif&notif_t=notify_me_page&notif_id=1468864358273870|title=The Devil Wears Prada|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=April 3, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/theprp/status/755116175063867392|title=The Devil Wears Prada announce new album and release date|publisher=[[Twitter]]|author=The PRP|date=July 18, 2016|accessdate=July 18, 2016}}</ref>{{better source|date=July 2016|reason=both primary sources}} Later on July 18, 2016, [[Giuseppe Capolupo]], drummer of [[Demise of Eros]], [[Haste the Day]] and [[Once Nothing]], stated he had recorded on ''Transit Blues''.<ref name=\"Instagram\">{{cite web|url=https://instagram.com/p/BIBTnpjBdB1JZRfzm0K8v0Q6RsRKuPHdnMb7_c0/|title=Giuseppe Capolupo announcement|publisher=[[Instagram]]|author=[[Once Nothing|Capolupo, Giuseppe]]|date=July 18, 2016|accessdate=July 18, 2016}}</ref> The band later released a video for \"To the Key of Evergreen\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://clrvynt.com/witness-the-rebirth-of-the-devil-wears-prada/|title=Witness the Rebirth of The Devil Wears Prada|publisher=Clrvynt|first=John|last=Hill|date=September 26, 2016|accessdate=September 28, 2016}}</ref> The album, ''Transit Blues'', was released October 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metalinjection.net/av/the-devil-wears-prada-stream-new-album-transit-blues|title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA Stream New Album, ''Transit Blues''|publisher=Metal Injection|first=Greg|last=Kennelty|date=October 7, 2016|accessdate=October 8, 2016}}</ref> Hranica recently was interviewed and when asked about adding Giuseppe Capolupo as an official member, he stated \"I totally perceive it being a permanent replacement if things go well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teamrock.com/feature/2016-10-06/the-devil-wears-prada-mike-hranica-transit-blues-interview|title=The Devil Wear's Prada's Mike Hrancia on anxiety, equality, and gun violence|publisher=[[Metal Hammer]]|first=Thea de|last=Gallier|date=October 6, 2016|accessdate=November 1, 2016}}</ref> In 2017, the band embarked on a tour with [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]] and [[Killswitch Engage]], called the \"Killthrax Tour\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/anthrax_killswitch_engage_the_devil_wears_prada_announce_the_killthrax_tour|title=Anthrax, Killswitch Engage, The Devil Wears Prada announce The Killthrax tour|publisher=[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]|first=Caitlyn|last=Ralph|date=December 14, 2016|accessdate=December 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn September 24, 2018, they signed with [[Solid State Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/the-devil-wears-prada-signs-with-solid-state-records/|title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA Signs With SOLID STATE RECORDS|date=September 24, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=September 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===''The Act'' (2019\u2013present)===\n\nIn 2019, Gering and Capolupo joined the band as official members.<ref name=\"label\"/> They proceeded to join in recording their seventh studio album ''[[The Act (album)|The Act]]'', with Gering providing songwriting and production duties, alongside producer Sonny DiPerri.<ref>{{cite web|title=THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA To Release 'The Act' Album In October|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/the-devil-wears-prada-to-release-the-act-album-in-october/|publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]]|accessdate=August 23, 2019|date=August 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Name==\nDespite speculations that the band named themselves after [[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|the film of the same title]], it turned out that they were formed before the film was released. They have explained that their band name is based on an anti-materialistic mindset and derived their name from [[The Devil Wears Prada (novel)|the novel, ''The Devil Wears Prada'']]. At the time of naming the band, the members assumed that the novel included anti-materialism as its moral, until later discovering that the novel did not feature this as its message at all.<ref name=\"highwiredaze.com\"/> Despite making this mistake, the band members refused to change the name and decided that they would create a new, [[materialism|non-materialistic]] definition indicating that at the [[Last Judgment]], God will not look at people's possessions.<ref name=\"highwiredaze.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://artists.letssingit.com/the-devil-wears-prada-6g9zn/biography |title=The Devil Wears Prada Biography |publisher=Artists.letssingit.com |date=May 28, 2013 |accessdate=May 16, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Current'''\n<!-- please do not change the order in which the members are listed; they are ordered first by year of joining, then alphabetically by surname -->\n* Jeremy DePoyster \u2013 rhythm guitar, vocals<!-- please do not change Jeremy DePoyster's position as vocals to clean vocals. DePoyster is not limited to melodic singing, as he has performed screams since the band's earliest demos, thanks. --> <small>(2005\u2013present)</small>\n* Mike Hranica \u2013 lead vocals<!-- please do not change Mike Hranica's position as lead vocals to unclean vocals, the vocals in almost every song is done by him, thanks. --> <small>(2005\u2013present)</small>, additional guitars <small>(2011\u2013present)</small>\n* Andy Trick \u2013 bass guitar <small>(2005\u2013present)</small>\n* Kyle Sipress \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals <small>(2015\u2013present)</small>\n* Jonathan Gering<ref name=\"label\">[https://www.solidstaterecords.com/the-devil-wears-prada Solid State Records TDWP]</ref> \u2013 keyboards, synthesizers, programming <small>(2019\u2013present, session member 2012\u20132019)</small>\n* [[Giuseppe Capolupo]]<ref name=\"label\"/> \u2013 drums <small>(2019\u2013present, session member 2016\u20132019)</small>\n'''Former'''\n* James Baney \u2013 keyboards, synthesizers, piano <small>(2005\u20132012)</small>\n* Chris Rubey \u2013 lead guitar <small>(2005\u20132015)</small>, backing vocals <small>(2011\u20132015)</small>\n* Daniel Williams \u2013 drums <small>(2005\u20132016)</small>\n\n{{col-2}}\n'''Former touring musicians'''\n* Samuel Penner<ref name=\"ITMOL\"/> \u2013 lead guitar <small>(2013)</small>\n* Mason Nagy<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bntjul3B1rS/|title=This is our pal Mason who's been filling in...|website=[[Instagram]]|date=September 14, 2018|accessdate=September 15, 2018|quote=This is our pal Mason who's been filling in on bass while Andy is home. Rochester tonight / Bethlehem, PA tomorrow. Bummed to miss Mrytle Beach the day after - to the folks down that way, our thoughts are with you, stay safe. Photo by @staceytakespictures}}</ref>  \u2013  bass guitar <small>(2018)</small>\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n'''Timeline'''\n{{#tag:timeline|\nImageSize  = width:800 height:auto barincrement:20\nPlotArea   = left:100 bottom:90 top:0 right:10\nAlignbars  = justify\nDateFormat = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod     = from:2005 till:12/30/2019\nScaleMajor = increment:2 start:2005\nScaleMinor = increment:1 start:2005\nTimeAxis   = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\nLegend     = orientation:vertical  columns:4  position:bottom\n\nColors =\n  id:UVocals  value:claret       legend:Unclean_vocals\n  id:CVocals  value:red          legend:Clean_vocals\n  id:Guitar   value:teal         legend:Lead_guitar\n  id:guitar2  value:brightgreen  legend:Rhythm_guitar\n  id:BVocals  value:pink         legend:Backing_vocals\n  id:Bass     value:blue         legend:Bass\n  id:drums    value:orange       legend:Drums\n  id:Keyboard value:purple       legend:Keyboards\n  id:album    value:black        legend:Studio_album\n  id:other    value:gray(0.55)   legend:Other_release\n  id:bars     value:gray(0.95)\n\nBackgroundColors=bars:bars\nLineData =\n layer:back\n color:album\n  at:08/22/2006\n  at:08/21/2007\n  at:05/05/2009\n  at:09/13/2011\n  at:09/17/2013\n  at:10/07/2016\n  at:10/11/2019\n color:other\n  at:08/23/2010\n  at:06/26/2012\n  at:08/21/2015\n\nBarData =\n  bar:Hranica    